What is a Network Load Balancer (NLB)?

AWS Elastic Load Balancer that operates at OSI Layer 4 (Transport layer)

Designed for:

Ultra-high performance

Ultra-low latency

Can handle millions of requests per second

Works with:

TCP

TLS

UDP

üìå Exam Trigger:
If the question mentions Layer 4, TCP, UDP, TLS, static IP, or extreme performance ‚Üí think NLB

2. Key Differences: ALB vs NLB (EXAM CLASSIC)
Feature	ALB	NLB
OSI Layer	Layer 7	Layer 4
Protocols	HTTP / HTTPS	TCP / TLS / UDP
Routing	Path / Host based	IP + Port based
Performance	High	Extremely High
Static IP	‚ùå	‚úî
Cookies	‚úî	‚ùå
Source IP preserved	‚ùå	‚úî
3. How NLB Works (Core Concepts)
Load Balancer Nodes

When you enable an AZ, NLB creates a node in that AZ

Each node routes traffic to targets

Cross-Zone Load Balancing

Disabled by default

‚ùå Without cross-zone:

Each NLB node sends traffic only to targets in its AZ

‚úî With cross-zone enabled:

Each node sends traffic to targets in all AZs

üìå Exam Tip:
NLB + uneven traffic + multi-AZ ‚Üí Enable cross-zone

4. Traffic Routing Logic
TCP / TLS Traffic

Uses flow hash algorithm based on:

Protocol

Source IP & Port

Destination IP & Port

Supports:

Long-lived TCP connections

WebSocket applications

UDP Traffic

Same flow (same source IP + port) ‚Üí always routed to the same target

Different UDP flows ‚Üí can go to different targets

üìå Exam Point:
UDP is connectionless, but NLB still ensures flow consistency

5. TLS with Network Load Balancer

NLB supports TLS listeners

Requires:

At least one server certificate

Can:

Terminate TLS

OR Pass-through encrypted traffic (end-to-end encryption)

üìå Exam Scenario:
If encryption must stay intact until the backend target ‚Üí NLB

6. Static IP & Elastic IP Support

NLB supports:

Static IP addresses

Elastic IPs (one per subnet)

Configured using subnet mappings

üìå Exam GOLD Rule:
If the question says ‚Äústatic IP required for load balancer‚Äù ‚Üí NLB

7. Common Architecture Scenarios (EXAM FAVORITES)
‚úÖ On-Premises to AWS

Distribute TCP traffic from on-prem servers

Use NLB for predictable IPs

‚úÖ Private SaaS (No Internet)

NLB + VPC Endpoint Service

Traffic stays inside AWS network

‚úÖ Firewall / Whitelisted IPs

NLB with Elastic IP

Firewall allows only known IPs

‚úÖ Cross-VPC / Cross-Account

Secure service-to-service communication

TLS pass-through

8. When to Choose Network Load Balancer

Choose NLB when you need:

TCP / UDP traffic

Static or Elastic IPs

Millions of requests per second

Low latency

Preserve client source IP

TLS pass-through or large-scale TLS termination

9. One-Line Exam Summary

Network Load Balancer is a Layer-4, ultra-fast load balancer that supports TCP, TLS, and UDP with static IPs and source-IP preservation.

‚úÖ PREDICTED MCQs (SAA-C03 ‚Äì HIGH PROBABILITY)
MCQ 1

Which load balancer operates at OSI Layer 4?

A. ALB
B. CLB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úÖ Answer: C

MCQ 2

An application requires static IP addresses and TCP traffic. Which load balancer should be used?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. Route 53

‚úÖ Answer: B

MCQ 3

Which protocol is supported by Network Load Balancer but not by Application Load Balancer?

A. HTTP
B. HTTPS
C. UDP
D. WebSocket

‚úÖ Answer: C

MCQ 4

Which load balancer preserves the client source IP address?

A. ALB
B. CLB
C. NLB
D. CloudFront

‚úÖ Answer: C

MCQ 5

Cross-zone load balancing for NLB is:

A. Enabled by default
B. Not supported
C. Disabled by default
D. Mandatory

‚úÖ Answer: C

MCQ 6

Which load balancer is BEST for millions of requests per second with low latency?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. GWLB
D. Classic

‚úÖ Answer: B

MCQ 7

Which load balancer should be used for UDP-based applications?

A. ALB
B. CLB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úÖ Answer: C

MCQ 8

A security team needs a load balancer with whitelisted IP addresses on firewalls. What should they use?

A. ALB
B. NLB with Elastic IP
C. CloudFront
D. Route 53

‚úÖ Answer: B

MCQ 9

Which NLB feature allows end-to-end encryption without decryption at the load balancer?

A. Sticky sessions
B. TLS pass-through
C. Path-based routing
D. Cookies

‚úÖ Answer: B

MCQ 10

Which routing method does an NLB use?

A. Path-based
B. Cookie-based
C. IP and Port-based
D. Header-based

‚úÖ Answer: C
